Barclays Wealth Appoints Gilbert as MENA Head, Replacing Nashaat

-- B y   S t e f a n i a   B i a n c h i
-- 
2011-07-24T14:02:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-24/barclays-wealth-appoints-gilbert-as-mena-head-replacing-nashaat.html
Rory Gilbert, the managing director
and head of high net worth business in the U.K. and Ireland at
Barclays Wealth, has been appointed as private banking head for
the  Middle East  and North Africa, replacing Soha Nashaat.  “We can confirm that Rory Gilbert has assumed the role
of head of Middle East and North Africa, International Private
Banking - EMEA at Barclays Wealth,” the bank said today in an
e-mailed statement in response to questions from Bloomberg News.
“Nashaat will be assuming a client and strategic advisory role
within Barclays Wealth.”  Nashaat had been the chief executive officer for Barclays
Wealth in Middle East and North Africa since 2006.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stefania Bianchi in Dubai at 
 sbianchi10@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
